---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/globals.css";
import { Header } from "../../components/Header";
import InnerPageCTA from "../../components/InnerPageCTA.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="September Product Innovations - New Features and Improvements - parcelLab"
  description="Campaign Manager, Returns Portal iOS integration, and additional product improvements from September 2023."
>
  <Header client:load />
  <main>
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section class="section-generous">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1440px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px]">
          <a href={`${b}/blog/`} class="group mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--ink-muted)] transition-colors hover:text-[#3D3AD3]">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-0.5"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
            Back to blog
          </a>
          <span class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[#3D3AD3]">Product Updates</span>
          <h1 class="text-display text-[var(--ink)]">September Product Innovations -- New Features and Improvements</h1>
          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">
            <span>By <strong class="font-medium text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Tinka Carrick</strong></span>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <time datetime="2023-10-11">October 11, 2023</time>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <span>6 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <section class="pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-lg">
          September brought exciting new capabilities to the parcelLab platform, headlined by the Campaign Manager launch and iOS integration for the Returns Portal. Here is a roundup of the latest product innovations.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Campaign Manager</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Campaign Manager is a new offering within parcelLab's Engage suite -- an intuitive, self-service content tool that empowers non-technical users to easily set up, run, and measure the impact of post-purchase marketing campaigns.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          The tool enables retailers to establish audience segments with statistical visibility for more targeted post-purchase communications designed to drive brand loyalty, engagement, and revenue.
        </p>

        <div class="my-10 rounded-2xl bg-[var(--surface-sunken)] p-8">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-[var(--ink-muted)]">Use Case Example</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            Jose, an eCommerce Operations Manager, faced challenges with orders exceeding EUR150 that were being held in Turkish customs. Using Campaign Manager, Jose targeted affected customers with text banners in emails and on tracking pages, directing them to a support resource with customs declaration details -- resolving numerous support inquiries and auto-returns.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">New Returns Portal Features</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Building on the Retain product suite launch, parcelLab added iOS integration to its Returns Portal. Customers can now manage return QR codes through Apple Wallet, enabling iPhone users to easily access personalized return information.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Additional Product Improvements</h2>

        <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">parcelLab Portal</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Enhanced user experience for editing and previewing message template changes. The Configurations module now allows automatic preview of changes to message-specific placeholders in the Email Editor. Campaign Manager enables editing multiple campaigns or audiences in filtered lists without re-adding filters.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Order Status Page</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Now displays zip code authentication forms for parcels marked as "Delivered," allowing end-customers to access protected information post-delivery.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Returns</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Retailers can configure probability percentages for the minimum/maximum return value feature, determining when label generation is prevented and specifying alternative actions like item retention or customer service contact.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="my-12 border-t border-[var(--line)]"></div>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          All features are now available, with some based on specific parcelLab product subscriptions. Contact your account manager or log into the parcelLab Portal for implementation guidance.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <InnerPageCTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
